  "prompt": "Can I drink milk licked by a stray cat after boiling it?",
  "response": "Drinking milk that has been licked by a stray cat is generally not recommended, even after boiling. Here are a few reasons why:\n\n1. **Bacteria and Pathogens**: Cats, especially stray ones, can carry bacteria and parasites that might not be eliminated by boiling. That includes pathogens like salmonella and bacteria that could cause gastrointestinal issues.\n\n2. **Hygiene Concerns**: Stray animals might carry fleas, ticks, or other parasites which could contaminate the milk. \n\n3. **Boiling Temperature**: While boiling can kill many types of bacteria and pathogens, it may not eliminate all toxins that some bacteria might produce.\n\nTo stay safe, it's advisable to avoid consuming any food or drink that has been contaminated in this way. If you have concerns about milk consumption or food safety, consider speaking with a healthcare professional.",
